<h1>Private Venue API — Frontend Integration Guide</h1>
<p><strong>Project:</strong> Destination Management (DMC)<br>
<strong>Document version:</strong> 1.0 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Date:</strong> May 2026<br>
<strong>Audience:</strong> Frontend developers integrating venue browse and booking into a React (or any HTTP) client.</p>

<h2>1. Overview</h2>
<p>This guide explains how to integrate the <strong>Private Venues</strong> module in your frontend application. The flow matches other DMC modules (guides, restaurants, transport):</p>
<ol>
<li>User logs in via OTP and receives a JWT token.</li>
<li>User browses venues (list + detail).</li>
<li>User adds one or more venues to a booking cart.</li>
<li>User submits a single API request with multiple <code>items</code> (multi-venue booking).</li>
<li>User views and cancels pending bookings from “My bookings”.</li>
</ol>
<p>All venue and booking endpoints require authentication (<code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code>), except OTP auth endpoints.</p>

<h2>2. Environment setup</h2>
<p>Create a <code>.env</code> file in your frontend project root:</p>
<pre>VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000</pre>
<p>All API paths below are relative to this base URL. Example full URL:</p>
<pre>http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/private-venues</pre>

<h2>3. Authentication (required first)</h2>
<p>Before calling venue APIs, obtain a JWT token.</p>

<h3>3.1 Send OTP</h3>
<pre>POST /api/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "identifier": "user@example.com"
}</pre>
<p><code>identifier</code> can be email or phone number registered in the system.</p>

<h3>3.2 Verify OTP</h3>
<pre>POST /api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "identifier": "user@example.com",
  "otp": "123456"
}</pre>
<p><strong>Success response (example):</strong></p>
<pre>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "token": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGc...",
    "user": { "id": 1, "name": "Jane Doe", "email": "user@example.com" }
  }
}</pre>
<p>Store the token (e.g. <code>localStorage.setItem('token', data.token)</code>) and send it on every venue request:</p>
<pre>Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGc...</pre>

<h2>4. HTTP client setup (Axios example)</h2>
<p>Recommended pattern used in <code>transport-frontend/src/api/axiosClient.jsx</code>:</p>
<pre>import axios from 'axios';

const axiosClient = axios.create({
  baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || 'http://127.0.0.1:8000',
  headers: { Accept: 'application/json', 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
});

axiosClient.interceptors.request.use((config) => {
  const token = localStorage.getItem('token');
  if (token) config.headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${token}`;
  return config;
});

axiosClient.interceptors.response.use(
  (res) => res,
  (error) => {
    if (error.response?.status === 401) {
      localStorage.removeItem('token');
      window.location.replace('/login');
    }
    return Promise.reject(error);
  }
);

export default axiosClient;</pre>

<h2>5. Venue APIs</h2>

<h3>5.1 List all venues</h3>
<pre>GET /api/private-venues</pre>
<p><strong>Query parameters (all optional):</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>city</td><td>string</td><td>Partial match on city</td></tr>
<tr><td>country</td><td>string</td><td>Partial match on country</td></tr>
<tr><td>venue_type</td><td>string</td><td>See venue types in section 8</td></tr>
<tr><td>event_type</td><td>string</td><td>Filter venues supporting this event type</td></tr>
<tr><td>min_guests</td><td>integer</td><td>Venues that can host at least this many guests</td></tr>
<tr><td>max_guests</td><td>integer</td><td>Venues whose minimum size is &lt;= this value</td></tr>
<tr><td>featured</td><td>boolean</td><td>Only featured venues when true</td></tr>
<tr><td>search</td><td>string</td><td>Search name, city, or brand chain</td></tr>
<tr><td>per_page</td><td>integer</td><td>Page size (default 15, max 100)</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>
<pre>GET /api/private-venues?city=Paris&amp;min_guests=50&amp;per_page=20</pre>

<p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>
<pre>{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Private venues retrieved successfully.",
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Grand Conference Hotel",
      "slug": "grand-conference-hotel",
      "venue_type": "hotel",
      "venue_type_label": "Hotel",
      "city": "Paris",
      "country": "France",
      "location_label": "Paris, France",
      "min_event_size": 10,
      "max_event_size": 500,
      "starting_daily_rate": 2500.00,
      "starting_rate_formatted": "€2,500.00",
      "currency": "EUR",
      "image": "https://example.com/storage/venues/1.jpg",
      "images": ["https://..."],
      "meeting_rooms_count": 12,
      "is_featured": true
    }
  ],
  "pagination": {
    "current_page": 1,
    "last_page": 3,
    "per_page": 20,
    "total": 45
  }
}</pre>

<p><strong>Frontend usage:</strong></p>
<pre>const res = await axiosClient.get('/api/private-venues', {
  params: { city: 'Paris', min_guests: 50, per_page: 20 }
});
const venues = res.data.data;</pre>

<h3>5.2 Get venue by ID</h3>
<pre>GET /api/private-venues/{id}</pre>
<p>Returns full venue profile including meeting spaces (rooms), contact info, and pricing notes.</p>

<p><strong>Example response (abbreviated):</strong></p>
<pre>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Grand Conference Hotel",
    "description": "...",
    "highlights": "...",
    "phone": "+33...",
    "email": "events@hotel.com",
    "website": "https://...",
    "pricing_notes": "...",
    "meeting_spaces": [
      {
        "id": 5,
        "name": "Ballroom A",
        "dimensions_label": "30m × 20m",
        "max_capacity": 400,
        "setup_capacities": {
          "theater": 400,
          "banquet": 250,
          "classroom": 180
        },
        "amenities": ["av_equipment", "natural_light"]
      }
    ]
  }
}</pre>

<p><strong>Frontend usage:</strong></p>
<pre>const res = await axiosClient.get(`/api/private-venues/${venueId}`);
const venue = res.data.data;</pre>

<h3>5.3 Filter options (for dropdowns)</h3>
<pre>GET /api/private-venues/filter-options</pre>
<p>Returns cities, countries, venue types, event types, and setup styles for building filter UI.</p>
<pre>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "cities": ["Paris", "London"],
    "countries": ["France", "UK"],
    "venue_types": { "hotel": "Hotel", "conference_center": "Conference center", ... },
    "event_types": { "conference": "Conference", "wedding": "Wedding", ... },
    "setup_styles": { "banquet": "Banquet rounds", "theater": "Theater", ... }
  }
}</pre>

<h2>6. Booking APIs</h2>

<h3>6.1 Create booking — single venue</h3>
<pre>POST /api/private-venue-bookings
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
<pre>{
  "private_venue_id": 1,
  "private_venue_space_id": 5,
  "event_date_start": "2026-06-15",
  "event_date_end": "2026-06-17",
  "guests": 120,
  "event_type": "conference",
  "setup_style": "banquet",
  "event_name": "Annual Sales Summit",
  "start_time": "09:00",
  "end_time": "18:00",
  "special_requests": "Need stage and breakout rooms",
  "contact_name": "Jane Doe",
  "contact_email": "jane@company.com",
  "contact_phone": "+33123456789"
}</pre>

<h3>6.2 Create booking — multiple venues (recommended for cart checkout)</h3>
<p>Send an <code>items</code> array. Each item is one venue booking. Shared contact fields can be at the root level.</p>
<pre>POST /api/private-venue-bookings
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
<pre>{
  "items": [
    {
      "private_venue_id": 1,
      "private_venue_space_id": 5,
      "event_date_start": "2026-06-15",
      "event_date_end": "2026-06-17",
      "guests": 120,
      "event_type": "conference",
      "setup_style": "banquet",
      "special_requests": "Main plenary room"
    },
    {
      "private_venue_id": 3,
      "event_date_start": "2026-06-15",
      "event_date_end": "2026-06-16",
      "guests": 80,
      "event_type": "corporate_event",
      "setup_style": "theater"
    }
  ],
  "contact_name": "Jane Doe",
  "contact_email": "jane@company.com",
  "contact_phone": "+33123456789"
}</pre>

<p><strong>Alternative shorthand</strong> (same dates/guests for all venues):</p>
<pre>{
  "private_venue_ids": [1, 3, 7],
  "event_date_start": "2026-06-15",
  "event_date_end": "2026-06-17",
  "guests": 100,
  "event_type": "conference"
}</pre>

<p><strong>Batch success response:</strong></p>
<pre>{
  "success": true,
  "message": "2 venue booking(s) submitted successfully.",
  "data": {
    "bookings": [ { "id": 10, "venue_name": "...", "status": "pending", ... } ],
    "count": 2,
    "combined_estimated_total": 7500.00
  }
}</pre>

<p><strong>Validation rules (per item):</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Field</th><th>Required</th><th>Rules</th></tr>
<tr><td>private_venue_id</td><td>Yes</td><td>Must exist and be active</td></tr>
<tr><td>private_venue_space_id</td><td>No</td><td>Must belong to the selected venue</td></tr>
<tr><td>event_date_start</td><td>Yes</td><td>Date, today or future</td></tr>
<tr><td>event_date_end</td><td>No</td><td>Defaults to start date if omitted</td></tr>
<tr><td>guests</td><td>Yes</td><td>Integer 1–50000; must fit venue min/max size</td></tr>
<tr><td>event_type</td><td>No</td><td>Must be a valid event type key (section 8)</td></tr>
<tr><td>setup_style</td><td>No</td><td>Must be a valid setup key (section 8)</td></tr>
<tr><td>start_time / end_time</td><td>No</td><td>Format HH:mm (24h)</td></tr>
<tr><td>special_requests</td><td>No</td><td>Free text</td></tr>
<tr><td>contact_*</td><td>No</td><td>Defaults to logged-in user profile</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="note">
<strong>Note:</strong> Users with account status <code>pending</code> receive HTTP 403 and cannot create bookings. Pending bookings can be cancelled; confirmed bookings cannot be cancelled via API.
</div>

<h3>6.3 List user bookings</h3>
<pre>GET /api/private-venue-bookings</pre>
<p><strong>Query parameters:</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>status</td><td><code>all</code> (default), <code>pending</code>, <code>confirmed</code>, <code>cancelled</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>per_page</td><td>Page size (default 15)</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>Example response item:</strong></p>
<pre>{
  "id": 10,
  "private_venue_id": 1,
  "venue_name": "Grand Conference Hotel",
  "venue_city": "Paris",
  "private_venue_space_id": 5,
  "space_name": "Ballroom A",
  "event_date_start": "2026-06-15",
  "event_date_end": "2026-06-17",
  "guests": 120,
  "setup_style": "banquet",
  "setup_style_label": "Banquet rounds",
  "estimated_total": 7500.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "status": "pending",
  "contact_name": "Jane Doe",
  "created_at": "2026-05-22T10:30:00.000000Z"
}</pre>

<h3>6.4 Get single booking</h3>
<pre>GET /api/private-venue-bookings/{id}</pre>
<p>Returns one booking belonging to the authenticated user.</p>

<h3>6.5 Cancel booking</h3>
<pre>POST /api/private-venue-bookings/{id}/cancel</pre>
<p>Cancels a <strong>pending</strong> booking. Already cancelled bookings return success with a message. Confirmed bookings return HTTP 400.</p>

<h2>7. Recommended frontend flow</h2>

<h3>7.1 Suggested routes</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>/login</td><td>OTP authentication</td></tr>
<tr><td>/private-venues</td><td>Venue listing with filters</td></tr>
<tr><td>/private-venues/checkout</td><td>Multi-venue cart checkout (define before /:id route)</td></tr>
<tr><td>/private-venues/:id</td><td>Venue detail page</td></tr>
<tr><td>/private-venue-bookings</td><td>User’s booking history</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.2 Cart pattern (multi-venue)</h3>
<ol>
<li>On list or detail page, user clicks “Add to cart”.</li>
<li>Store minimal venue objects in <code>localStorage</code> (id, name, city, country).</li>
<li>On checkout, fetch full venue details for each cart item to populate meeting room dropdowns.</li>
<li>Build the <code>items</code> array from per-venue form fields.</li>
<li>POST to <code>/api/private-venue-bookings</code>.</li>
<li>Clear cart and redirect to bookings list on success.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Example cart helper:</strong></p>
<pre>const CART_KEY = 'dmc_private_venue_cart';

export function getVenueCart() {
  return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(CART_KEY) || '[]');
}

export function addVenueToCart(venue) {
  const cart = getVenueCart();
  if (!cart.some(v => v.id === venue.id)) {
    cart.push({ id: venue.id, name: venue.name, city: venue.city, country: venue.country });
    localStorage.setItem(CART_KEY, JSON.stringify(cart));
  }
}</pre>

<p><strong>Example checkout submit:</strong></p>
<pre>const items = cart.map(v => ({
  private_venue_id: v.id,
  event_date_start: forms[v.id].event_date_start,
  event_date_end: forms[v.id].event_date_end || forms[v.id].event_date_start,
  guests: Number(forms[v.id].guests),
  event_type: forms[v.id].event_type || undefined,
  setup_style: forms[v.id].setup_style || undefined,
  private_venue_space_id: forms[v.id].spaceId ? Number(forms[v.id].spaceId) : undefined,
  special_requests: forms[v.id].special_requests || undefined,
}));

await axiosClient.post('/api/private-venue-bookings', {
  items,
  contact_name: contact.name,
  contact_email: contact.email,
  contact_phone: contact.phone,
});</pre>

<h3>7.3 Unified dashboard (optional)</h3>
<p>All module bookings (including venues) are also available via:</p>
<pre>GET /api/my-bookings?module=private_venue</pre>

<h2>8. Reference — enum values</h2>

<h3>Venue types (<code>venue_type</code>)</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Key</th><th>Label</th></tr>
<tr><td>hotel</td><td>Hotel</td></tr>
<tr><td>conference_center</td><td>Conference center</td></tr>
<tr><td>convention_center</td><td>Convention center</td></tr>
<tr><td>restaurant</td><td>Restaurant / private dining</td></tr>
<tr><td>unique_space</td><td>Unique space</td></tr>
<tr><td>museum</td><td>Museum / gallery</td></tr>
<tr><td>outdoor</td><td>Outdoor venue</td></tr>
<tr><td>other</td><td>Other</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Event types (<code>event_type</code>)</h3>
<p>meeting, conference, corporate_event, incentive, wedding, social, exhibition, training, gala</p>

<h3>Setup styles (<code>setup_style</code>)</h3>
<p>theater, classroom, banquet, u_shape, conference, reception, hollow_square, cabaret</p>

<h3>Booking status</h3>
<p>pending → confirmed (by admin) or cancelled (by user while pending)</p>

<h2>9. Error handling</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>HTTP code</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Frontend action</th></tr>
<tr><td>401</td><td>Missing or expired token</td><td>Redirect to login</td></tr>
<tr><td>403</td><td>Account pending approval</td><td>Show message; disable booking</td></tr>
<tr><td>404</td><td>Venue or booking not found</td><td>Show not-found UI</td></tr>
<tr><td>422</td><td>Validation error</td><td>Display <code>errors</code> object or <code>message</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>400</td><td>Business rule (e.g. cancel confirmed)</td><td>Show <code>message</code> to user</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>422 example:</strong></p>
<pre>{
  "success": false,
  "message": "The items.0.guests field is required.",
  "errors": {
    "items.0.guests": ["The items.0.guests field is required."]
  }
}</pre>

<h2>10. Reference implementation</h2>
<p>Working example pages exist in the project:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>transport-frontend/src/api/axiosClient.jsx</code> — HTTP client with JWT</li>
<li><code>transport-frontend/src/pages/PrivateVenuePage.jsx</code> — List + filters + cart</li>
<li><code>transport-frontend/src/pages/PrivateVenueDetails.jsx</code> — Detail view</li>
<li><code>transport-frontend/src/pages/PrivateVenueCheckout.jsx</code> — Multi-venue submit</li>
<li><code>transport-frontend/src/pages/PrivateVenueBookings.jsx</code> — List + cancel</li>
<li><code>transport-frontend/src/utils/venueCart.js</code> — Cart localStorage helpers</li>
</ul>

<h2>11. Quick checklist</h2>
<ul>
<li>Set <code>VITE_API_URL</code> in frontend <code>.env</code></li>
<li>Implement OTP login; store JWT token</li>
<li>Attach <code>Authorization: Bearer</code> header on all venue requests</li>
<li>Build list page with <code>GET /api/private-venues</code></li>
<li>Build detail page with <code>GET /api/private-venues/{id}</code></li>
<li>Implement cart + checkout with <code>POST /api/private-venue-bookings</code> and <code>items[]</code></li>
<li>Build bookings page with <code>GET /api/private-venue-bookings</code></li>
<li>Wire cancel with <code>POST /api/private-venue-bookings/{id}/cancel</code></li>
<li>Handle 401, 403, and 422 responses in UI</li>
</ul>

